WEBVTT

1
00:00:04.892 --> 00:00:06.883
Marietta Yuby.

2
00:00:09.163 --> 00:00:13.031
From the time I met her
in the seventh grade...

3
00:00:13.100 --> 00:00:15.261
that was my sweetheart.

4
00:00:16.537 --> 00:00:18.562
She didn't
make it easy though.

5
00:00:18.639 --> 00:00:22.006
Took me all the way till the eighth grade
to catch up with her.

6
00:00:22.076 --> 00:00:24.476
[ Chuckles ]
She's beautiful.

7
00:00:24.545 --> 00:00:26.479
Yeah.

8
00:00:26.547 --> 00:00:29.744
She passed away
shortly after we were married.

9
00:00:32.353 --> 00:00:34.344
I'm really sorry.

10
00:00:36.857 --> 00:00:39.951
The greatest gift
she gave me...

11
00:00:40.027 --> 00:00:42.894
was the will to move on...

12
00:00:42.963 --> 00:00:44.954
to overcome.

13
00:00:47.701 --> 00:00:50.670
You know. I may have
met someone myself.

14
00:00:50.738 --> 00:00:54.196
Then cherish her.

15
00:00:54.275 --> 00:00:57.676
And become
the man she deserves.

16
00:01:01.348 --> 00:01:03.339
Have a seat.

17
00:01:04.818 --> 00:01:06.752
Now. as I said...

18
00:01:06.820 --> 00:01:10.119
I had a feeling
you were gonna stop by.

19
00:01:13.427 --> 00:01:18.126
That university you attended-
What was it rated? Number three?

20
00:01:18.198 --> 00:01:20.189
Number-three party school
in the country.

21
00:01:21.802 --> 00:01:25.067
Do- Do you truly
know how to learn?

22
00:01:25.139 --> 00:01:28.006
 Jason. any process
worth going through...

23
00:01:28.075 --> 00:01:31.010
will get tougher
before it gets easier.

24
00:01:31.078 --> 00:01:34.479
That's what makes
learning a gift...

25
00:01:34.548 --> 00:01:36.539
even if pain
is your teacher.

26
00:01:59.306 --> 00:02:01.570
No. There's no way.

27
00:02:01.642 --> 00:02:04.577
Anywhere but there.

28
00:02:04.645 --> 00:02:07.170
I know what he's trying to do.
and it's not gonna work.

29
00:02:07.247 --> 00:02:09.579
He can take his millions
to his grave. I don't care.

30
00:02:09.650 --> 00:02:13.245
What he's trying to do is for your benefit.
not your destruction.

31
00:02:14.989 --> 00:02:17.583
You know. Hamilton.
you sound just like him.

32
00:02:17.658 --> 00:02:19.990
But guess what.
You're not him.

33
00:02:21.061 --> 00:02:23.222
I don't know. son.

34
00:02:23.297 --> 00:02:25.595
I do have one of his kidneys.

35
00:02:28.435 --> 00:02:30.926
[ Emily ]
He's been out there for hours.

36
00:02:31.005 --> 00:02:33.667
[ Alexia ]
Yep. He's got some big decisions to make.

37
00:02:33.741 --> 00:02:37.177
Do you think he'll
come in or go home?

38
00:02:40.114 --> 00:02:42.105
He doesn't have a home.

39
00:02:42.182 --> 00:02:45.674
[ Emily ]
You're right. She hates you.

40
00:02:47.054 --> 00:02:50.785
- I know.
- Then why are you here?

41
00:02:50.858 --> 00:02:53.156
I have to leave the country
for a while.

42
00:02:53.227 --> 00:02:55.593
I'm reluctant to go because
of what I'm leaving behind.

43
00:02:55.663 --> 00:02:57.893
What are you leaving behind?

44
00:03:04.238 --> 00:03:07.901
Then you have to go.
Now get out of here.

45
00:03:09.943 --> 00:03:11.968
You screwed up big time.
you know!

46
00:03:12.046 --> 00:03:17.348
I had to eat a rubber hospital
turkey for Thanksgiving!

47
00:03:22.356 --> 00:03:25.792
You better be back
by Christmas!

48
00:03:42.142 --> 00:03:44.667
[ Children Laughing ]

49
00:03:53.287 --> 00:03:55.278
[ Bleating ]

50
00:04:13.173 --> 00:04:16.700
[ Scoffs ]
Even down here. you put your name on everything.

51
00:04:16.777 --> 00:04:19.644
Welcome! Oh. welcome!

52
00:04:19.713 --> 00:04:21.647
 Jason Stevens.

53
00:04:21.715 --> 00:04:25.116
Oh! Oh!
So good to meet you.

54
00:04:25.185 --> 00:04:27.278
- I'm Bella.
- Hi.

55
00:04:27.354 --> 00:04:31.950
May I be the first to show you
inside the library your grandfather built?

56
00:04:34.094 --> 00:04:36.028
- Yeah. sure.
- Oh. good. good.

57
00:04:40.100 --> 00:04:42.466
Where are all the books?

58
00:04:42.536 --> 00:04:45.130
Oh. [ Chuckles ]
You joke.

59
00:04:45.205 --> 00:04:47.139
W-With the people.

60
00:04:48.642 --> 00:04:53.272
Is it not like that in the great libraries
de Los Estados Unidos?

61
00:04:56.650 --> 00:04:59.414
Villagers wait for books.

62
00:04:59.486 --> 00:05:01.477
You bring them new books.

63
00:05:01.555 --> 00:05:06.151
They are waiting for you
to pick up old books.

64
00:05:06.226 --> 00:05:10.185
Exchange. Library. ¿S¡?

65
00:05:12.666 --> 00:05:14.600
[ Exhales ]

66
00:05:14.668 --> 00:05:17.933
So basically.
I'm in a third world country...

67
00:05:18.005 --> 00:05:20.473
at a backwards library
with no books.

68
00:05:21.608 --> 00:05:23.803
And the books that are here.
I can't even read.

69
00:05:23.877 --> 00:05:25.970
[ Book Closes ]

70
00:05:26.046 --> 00:05:28.037
Great.

71
00:05:31.418 --> 00:05:33.409
Mmm.

72
00:05:42.229 --> 00:05:46.188
This I found
when I was cleaning his desk...

73
00:05:46.266 --> 00:05:48.962
once I heard
of Red's passing.

74
00:05:49.036 --> 00:05:51.061
I thought maybe you
would like to keep.

75
00:05:54.041 --> 00:05:56.168
When you sent this to him...

76
00:05:56.243 --> 00:06:00.009
he proudly showed it
to all of us.

77
00:06:00.080 --> 00:06:02.071
Then the tragedy.

78
00:06:03.717 --> 00:06:05.708
It broke his heart.

79
00:06:10.023 --> 00:06:12.184
[ Young  Jason's Voice ]
Dear Grandpa...

80
00:06:12.259 --> 00:06:14.250
How's Ecuador?

81
00:06:14.328 --> 00:06:16.956
I miss you and Dad so much.

82
00:06:17.030 --> 00:06:19.692
You know. my birthday's
coming up. and I was thinking...

83
00:06:19.766 --> 00:06:22.098
instead of giving me gifts
this year...

84
00:06:22.169 --> 00:06:24.603
could you take me
on one of your trips?

85
00:06:24.671 --> 00:06:27.640
I promise I won't
cause any trouble.

86
00:06:27.708 --> 00:06:30.575
I just want to see you
and Dad again soon.

87
00:06:30.644 --> 00:06:33.772
Write back. please.
Love. Jason.

88
00:06:33.847 --> 00:06:35.838
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

89
00:06:50.831 --> 00:06:52.799
- [ Chattering In Spanish ]
- Hola.

90
00:06:56.904 --> 00:06:59.429
[ Children Laughing ]

91
00:07:07.948 --> 00:07:09.939
Un momento. por favor.

92
00:07:11.919 --> 00:07:13.978
You look
just like your father.

93
00:07:17.090 --> 00:07:19.024
I was here
the night he died.

94
00:07:25.999 --> 00:07:27.990
It happened up on that mountain.
didn't it?

95
00:07:31.405 --> 00:07:33.396
- Take me there.
- You cannot go.

96
00:07:33.473 --> 00:07:35.407
It is now the province
of the drug lords.

97
00:07:35.475 --> 00:07:38.000
You don't understand.

98
00:07:38.078 --> 00:07:41.980
I'll pay you.
Well. someday.

99
00:07:42.049 --> 00:07:45.746
I understand perfectly.
But. señor. I only have one life.

100
00:07:45.819 --> 00:07:48.583
You're just bargaining now.
aren't you?

101
00:07:48.655 --> 00:07:53.115
Señor Stevens.
you do not want to pay the price it would take.

102
00:07:53.193 --> 00:07:56.185
No one
who goes there returns.

103
00:07:56.263 --> 00:07:58.390
- [ Children Shouting ]
- [ Footsteps Approaching ]

104
00:07:58.465 --> 00:08:00.262
[ Speaking Spanish ]

105
00:08:00.334 --> 00:08:06.204
Our guest of honor.
Mr. Jason Stevens.

106
00:08:22.656 --> 00:08:25.750
Oh.
Gracias.

107
00:08:25.826 --> 00:08:28.021
[ Chuckles ]
I'm afraid to ask.

108
00:08:28.095 --> 00:08:30.586
Oh. you will love it.

109
00:08:30.664 --> 00:08:32.859
It's so rare we catch one.

110
00:08:32.933 --> 00:08:36.960
- The chief is going to talk.
- Oh.

111
00:08:44.845 --> 00:08:47.905
He says we are here
to celebrate you...

112
00:08:47.981 --> 00:08:51.644
and those who keep
theJay Stevens Library alive.

113
00:08:51.718 --> 00:08:54.186
- [ All Cheering ]
- Oh. no. no. no. no. no. no. no.

114
00:08:54.254 --> 00:08:58.384
No. No. No. no. no.
He must be mistaken.

115
00:08:58.458 --> 00:09:01.393
My grandfather was very generous.
Everything's named after him.

116
00:09:01.461 --> 00:09:06.330
No. it is theJay Stevens
Memorial Library.

117
00:09:06.400 --> 00:09:08.834
[ Speaking Spanish ]

118
00:09:08.902 --> 00:09:10.836
[ Laughs.
Speaking Spanish ]

119
00:09:10.904 --> 00:09:12.895
[ Crowd Cheering. Applauding ]

120
00:09:18.412 --> 00:09:20.403
To my father.

121
00:09:20.480 --> 00:09:22.505
-Salud.
-Salud.

122
00:09:28.422 --> 00:09:31.619
- [ Speaking Spanish ]
- Have some more.

123
00:09:33.894 --> 00:09:36.419
- Salud.
- Salud.

124
00:09:38.398 --> 00:09:39.956
Salud.

125
00:09:41.868 --> 00:09:43.859
[ Laughing ]

126
00:09:45.272 --> 00:09:47.604
[ Laughing Continues ]

127
00:09:51.845 --> 00:09:53.836
[ Goat Bleating ]

128
00:09:59.286 --> 00:10:01.777
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

129
00:10:30.150 --> 00:10:32.482
You cannot hope
to find it without me.

130
00:10:33.487 --> 00:10:35.648
How'd you know I'd go?

131
00:10:35.722 --> 00:10:38.520
You are a Stevens.
are you not?

132
00:10:38.592 --> 00:10:41.186
I thought you said
you couldn't take me.

133
00:10:42.796 --> 00:10:46.493
My purpose in coming to you
was a promise I made to Señor Red-

134
00:10:48.502 --> 00:10:50.470
that you could
learn the truth.

135
00:10:50.537 --> 00:10:52.664
He had one desire
and one desire alone-

136
00:10:52.739 --> 00:10:54.673
to ask your forgiveness.

137
00:11:00.714 --> 00:11:03.274
[ Man ]
He said one day you would come.

138
00:11:03.350 --> 00:11:05.341
Only then you could
learn the truth.

139
00:11:05.418 --> 00:11:08.216
Stop! Stop the jeep.

140
00:11:30.944 --> 00:11:32.969
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

141
00:12:32.606 --> 00:12:34.801
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

142
00:12:45.885 --> 00:12:48.012
[ Sniffling ]

143
00:12:52.692 --> 00:12:54.683
[ Sniffles ]

144
00:12:59.299 --> 00:13:02.632
He had learned of a village
in the next valley...

145
00:13:02.702 --> 00:13:05.068
that had a plague and needed
medical supplies.

146
00:13:06.806 --> 00:13:09.707
But he never understood
why Red forbid him to go.

147
00:13:09.776 --> 00:13:13.473
There was no plague.
There was no village.

148
00:13:13.546 --> 00:13:16.242
What?

149
00:13:16.316 --> 00:13:20.013
Red wanted to introduce
your father to the oil business.

150
00:13:20.086 --> 00:13:22.850
But your father...

151
00:13:22.922 --> 00:13:25.117
was restless and bored.

152
00:13:25.191 --> 00:13:27.591
- No. No.
- He snuck away. He ran away...

153
00:13:27.661 --> 00:13:30.061
- and took a plane he had no business taking.
- No.

154
00:13:30.130 --> 00:13:34.328
This is what Red wanted
to protect you from. Till now.

155
00:13:34.401 --> 00:13:36.926
There can be no blame
for what happened here.

156
00:13:37.003 --> 00:13:39.699
The penalty for
your father's impulsiveness...

157
00:13:39.773 --> 00:13:41.900
unfortunately. was a life-

158
00:13:41.975 --> 00:13:44.375
- [ Thunder Rumbling ]
- his.

159
00:14:01.294 --> 00:14:05.025
- ¿Americano?
- [ Speaking Spanish ]

160
00:14:28.488 --> 00:14:31.150
- [ Thunderclap ]
- [ Men Shout In Spanish ]

161
00:14:32.325 --> 00:14:34.589
Ow.
[ Gasping ]

162
00:14:34.661 --> 00:14:36.595
[ Man Shouting In Spanish ]

163
00:14:36.663 --> 00:14:38.654
[ Men Laughing ]

164
00:14:41.901 --> 00:14:43.892
[ Laughing Continues ]

165
00:15:06.493 --> 00:15:08.484
[ Coughing. Yetching ]

166
00:15:11.331 --> 00:15:13.424
[ Paper Rustling ]

167
00:15:33.853 --> 00:15:36.344
[ Reading In Spanish ]

168
00:15:39.759 --> 00:15:44.958
[ Man ]
''It was the best of times. it was the worst of times...

169
00:15:45.031 --> 00:15:48.330
''it was the age of wisdom...

170
00:15:48.401 --> 00:15:51.199
it was the age
of foolishness. ''

171
00:15:54.541 --> 00:15:57.066
Can't you find him?

172
00:15:57.143 --> 00:16:00.738
We think that
he went searching for the crash site...

173
00:16:00.814 --> 00:16:03.180
which is in
lawless territory.

174
00:16:03.249 --> 00:16:06.514
- I'm sorry. Crash site?
- Where his father died.

175
00:16:08.288 --> 00:16:11.655
Well. I mean. is-
is he in any danger?

176
00:16:15.428 --> 00:16:17.362
I'm so sorry.

177
00:16:17.430 --> 00:16:22.197
[ Reading In Spanish ]

178
00:16:22.268 --> 00:16:25.294
[ Man ]
''Neither love. nor hate thy life.'

179
00:16:25.371 --> 00:16:28.807
''but what thou livest.
live well...

180
00:16:28.875 --> 00:16:32.743
however long or short
may the heavens permit. ''

181
00:16:38.218 --> 00:16:40.209
Tell me about my father.

182
00:16:41.588 --> 00:16:45.581
In many ways. he was
very similar to you-

183
00:16:45.658 --> 00:16:50.459
restless. rebellious.
angry.

184
00:16:50.530 --> 00:16:53.397
I think Red
saw something in him...

185
00:16:53.466 --> 00:16:57.163
that he didn't see
in his other sons-

186
00:16:57.237 --> 00:16:59.228
a fire.

187
00:17:00.240 --> 00:17:03.903
The same fire
he sees in you.

188
00:17:13.186 --> 00:17:15.177
I still don't forgive you.

189
00:17:17.156 --> 00:17:20.148
- [ Door Opens ]
- [ Men Shouting In Spanish ]

190
00:17:23.730 --> 00:17:26.722
[ Shouting Continues ]

191
00:17:29.302 --> 00:17:31.827
[ Men Laughing ]

192
00:17:31.905 --> 00:17:34.840
- [ Blows Landing ]
- [ Man Groaning ]

193
00:17:46.252 --> 00:17:48.482
[ Man Shouts In Spanish ]

194
00:17:55.028 --> 00:17:57.292
Amigo? Amigo.
are you here?

195
00:18:01.701 --> 00:18:04.602
- [ Man Shouts In Spanish ]
- [ Gasping ]

196
00:18:10.209 --> 00:18:13.440
No. no. no! No! No. no!
Please. no! I can- I can pay you!

197
00:18:13.513 --> 00:18:15.674
- I have money! Please!
- [ Shouts In Spanish ]

198
00:18:15.748 --> 00:18:17.841
- Oh. God! God! Does anyone
understand what I'm saying?
- [ Gunshot ]

199
00:18:17.917 --> 00:18:20.715
[ Gasping ]

200
00:18:30.196 --> 00:18:32.721
[ Speaking Spanish ]

201
00:18:32.799 --> 00:18:34.494
[ All Laugh ]

202
00:18:34.567 --> 00:18:36.398
[ Sobbing ]

203
00:18:36.469 --> 00:18:38.403
[ Laughter Continues ]

204
00:18:39.706 --> 00:18:41.697
[ Sobbing ]

205
00:18:42.709 --> 00:18:44.677
[ Groans ]

206
00:18:52.051 --> 00:18:54.679
[ Men Chattering In Spanish ]

207
00:18:58.091 --> 00:19:01.219
[ Speaking Spanish ]

208
00:19:03.596 --> 00:19:05.689
[ Men Shouting In Spanish ]

209
00:19:09.302 --> 00:19:11.236
[ Grunts ]

210
00:19:11.304 --> 00:19:15.502
[ Man Mumbling In Spanish ]

211
00:19:16.509 --> 00:19:18.500
- [ Man Grunts ]
- [ Body Thuds ]

212
00:19:30.623 --> 00:19:32.614
''Mueren. '' ''Mueren. ''

213
00:19:35.962 --> 00:19:38.362
Muerte.

214
00:19:38.431 --> 00:19:40.422
Death.

215
00:19:57.950 --> 00:20:00.418
[ Snoring ]

216
00:20:32.085 --> 00:20:34.076
[ Panting ]

217
00:20:46.299 --> 00:20:48.529
Hey. Hey.

218
00:20:48.601 --> 00:20:51.934
Hey. Shh.

219
00:20:52.004 --> 00:20:54.302
- [ Jason ] Can you walk?
- [ Fly Buzzing ]

220
00:20:55.374 --> 00:20:57.308
Save yourself.

221
00:20:57.376 --> 00:20:59.310
Not on your life.
Come on.

222
00:20:59.378 --> 00:21:01.369
[ Grunting ]

223
00:21:04.383 --> 00:21:07.511
[ Men Shouting In Distance ]

224
00:21:07.587 --> 00:21:09.578
[ Gunfire In Distance ]

225
00:21:11.023 --> 00:21:12.957
Come on.

226
00:21:13.025 --> 00:21:14.993
Come on.

227
00:21:17.063 --> 00:21:19.759
[ Gunfire ]

228
00:21:46.726 --> 00:21:49.388
Hey. Oh. Mmm.

229
00:21:49.462 --> 00:21:51.453
What are you
doing here?

230
00:21:52.498 --> 00:21:54.489
I was scared to death.

231
00:21:56.302 --> 00:21:58.236
Where's Emily?

232
00:21:58.304 --> 00:22:00.704
Um. she's resting.
She'll see you tomorrow.

233
00:22:00.773 --> 00:22:02.764
You guys have
a good Christmas?

234
00:22:02.842 --> 00:22:05.606
We didn't have one.
How could we?

235
00:22:07.613 --> 00:22:11.777
You know what? We're gonna have
a fantastic one next year.

236
00:22:11.851 --> 00:22:13.842
I promise.

237
00:22:18.591 --> 00:22:20.923
We won't have a next year.

238
00:23:14.347 --> 00:23:19.410
[ Red's Voice ] The events of that day
play in my mind over and over and over again.

239
00:23:19.485 --> 00:23:21.248
I'm so sorry.

240
00:23:21.320 --> 00:23:24.653
If your father hadn't died
while working for me-

241
00:23:24.724 --> 00:23:26.658
Please give me
a chance to explain.

242
00:23:26.726 --> 00:23:31.425
Ever since that day. my life
has been filled with grief.

243
00:23:32.832 --> 00:23:35.198
It is apparent that you
will never forgive me.

244
00:23:37.503 --> 00:23:40.097
I do not blame you for this.

245
00:23:40.172 --> 00:23:42.606
It's also something
that I cannot do for myself.

246
00:23:44.377 --> 00:23:47.175
I loved your father
so much.

247
00:23:47.246 --> 00:23:52.445
Aparent should never have
a child precede them in death.

248
00:23:52.518 --> 00:23:56.545
It is the most painful
experience imaginable.

249
00:23:56.622 --> 00:23:58.613
Uh...

250
00:24:00.259 --> 00:24:02.625
that's enough for today.
gentlemen.

251
00:24:19.679 --> 00:24:21.738
Welcome back. stranger.

252
00:24:21.814 --> 00:24:24.510
Hey.

253
00:24:35.094 --> 00:24:37.028
Ta-da.

254
00:24:37.096 --> 00:24:39.087
Here.

255
00:24:45.905 --> 00:24:47.930
Wow.

256
00:24:48.007 --> 00:24:50.202
An ''airport gift shop'' gift.

257
00:24:50.276 --> 00:24:54.235
- How thoughtful.
- [ Chuckles ]

258
00:24:54.313 --> 00:24:56.247
Does it come
with needles?

259
00:24:56.315 --> 00:24:59.113
[ Chuckling ]

260
00:24:59.185 --> 00:25:01.176
Uh-

261
00:25:04.590 --> 00:25:07.787
Yeah. you can kiss me.
even though you're a guy.

262
00:25:12.398 --> 00:25:14.389
I missed you too.

263
00:25:15.935 --> 00:25:18.597
Whatever.
Let's cut to the chase.

264
00:25:19.672 --> 00:25:22.004
You really blew it
with us this Christmas.

265
00:25:22.074 --> 00:25:24.941
I was unavoidably detained.

266
00:25:25.011 --> 00:25:26.945
Okay. yeah.

267
00:25:27.013 --> 00:25:29.004
I want Christmas.

268
00:25:32.251 --> 00:25:34.742
I want to ride a horse.

269
00:25:36.088 --> 00:25:40.081
Oh. I got. like. a week or two
left with this other thing...

270
00:25:40.159 --> 00:25:42.684
but. um. let me make a call
and we'll see-

271
00:25:42.762 --> 00:25:44.753
 Jason.

272
00:25:46.332 --> 00:25:48.323
Now.

273
00:25:49.368 --> 00:25:51.268
Okay.

274
00:25:51.470 --> 00:25:55.338
- That works for me.
- Excuse me. sir. It's  Jason on line two.

275
00:25:55.408 --> 00:25:57.672
Oh. uh.
will you all excuse me?

276
00:25:57.743 --> 00:26:00.337
I have to take this call.

277
00:26:03.315 --> 00:26:05.579
- [ Phone Beeps ]
- Go ahead. Jason.

278
00:26:05.651 --> 00:26:08.176
[ Jason ] Mr. Hamilton. look.
One way or another. this is over.

279
00:26:08.254 --> 00:26:10.188
Either I was in South America
way too long...

280
00:26:10.256 --> 00:26:12.747
or I missed the deadline
or whatever...

281
00:26:12.825 --> 00:26:15.487
but what I'm about to do
is way more important.

282
00:26:15.561 --> 00:26:17.995
And I know you have no reason
whatsoever to trust me...

283
00:26:18.064 --> 00:26:21.830
but I need to borrow
my grandfather's jet.

284
00:26:22.835 --> 00:26:25.770
And I need it now.

285
00:26:25.838 --> 00:26:29.330
I want to take Alexia and Emily to Gus's ranch
for a late Christmas.

286
00:26:29.408 --> 00:26:32.434
 Jason. do you know what you're doing?
Look. I have no control-

287
00:26:32.511 --> 00:26:36.675
Uh. what. um. Mr. Hamilton
was saying was that. uh...

288
00:26:36.749 --> 00:26:41.550
he'll be sending along
Red's next gift on your Conversay.

289
00:26:41.620 --> 00:26:43.747
You have your bags
packed within the hour...

290
00:26:43.823 --> 00:26:46.815
and. uh. he will
have the jet fueled...

291
00:26:46.892 --> 00:26:48.826
- and ready to go.
- [ Jason ] Thank you.

292
00:26:48.894 --> 00:26:51.829
This means so much to me.
And. Hamilton...

293
00:26:51.897 --> 00:26:55.128
I promise I'm gonna take back all those
nasty thoughts about you being the Grinch.

294
00:26:57.369 --> 00:27:00.065
Thanks again. Merry Christmas.
[ Exhales ]

295
00:27:00.139 --> 00:27:03.597
[ Emily. Jason. Alexia
Singing Christmas Song ]

296
00:27:06.946 --> 00:27:08.880
Hey. Gus!

297
00:27:11.817 --> 00:27:13.808
What is this?
Snow in Texas?

298
00:27:13.886 --> 00:27:17.583
Had it trucked in.
Ho. ho. ho!

299
00:27:19.458 --> 00:27:21.858
- All right. Hector. hit it!
- [ Gasps ]

300
00:27:21.927 --> 00:27:24.987
- [ Chuckling ]
- [ Gasps ]

301
00:27:25.064 --> 00:27:27.589
- Merry Christmas.
- Gus. this is Emily.

302
00:27:27.666 --> 00:27:30.396
- Hi. Emily. Welcome.
- Alexia.

303
00:27:30.469 --> 00:27:33.336
- Hi.
- Alexia. how ya doin'?

304
00:27:33.405 --> 00:27:35.498
- And there he is.
- Hey.

305
00:27:35.574 --> 00:27:38.338
[ Chuckles ]
I'll get your bags.

306
00:27:53.926 --> 00:27:56.986
[ Alexia ]
I see why you chose this place.

307
00:27:57.062 --> 00:27:59.087
[ Jason ]
I wish I could take the credit.

308
00:27:59.165 --> 00:28:02.396
Emily said her wish was to go
horseback riding with you.

309
00:28:03.636 --> 00:28:05.570
What?

310
00:28:05.638 --> 00:28:07.868
Emily-
[ Crying ]

311
00:28:07.940 --> 00:28:09.931
What? What's wrong?

312
00:28:12.611 --> 00:28:14.602
She's-

313
00:28:15.614 --> 00:28:17.912
She's terrified of horses.

314
00:28:19.919 --> 00:28:21.910
I'm the one who loves horses.

315
00:28:25.591 --> 00:28:27.582
[ Alexia ]
Oh. Jason. it's so beautiful.

316
00:28:27.660 --> 00:28:29.651
Thank you.
Thank you.

317
00:28:52.251 --> 00:28:54.617
[ Gus ]
Well. this is what I was tellin' you about.

318
00:28:54.687 --> 00:28:57.349
- Pretty. huh?
- [ Jason ] It's beautiful.

319
00:28:59.325 --> 00:29:01.953
Hey. come here.
I wanna show you something.

320
00:29:02.027 --> 00:29:04.018
Gonna be okay. sweetie?

321
00:29:21.013 --> 00:29:22.947
Alexia...

322
00:29:23.015 --> 00:29:26.678
- there's something I need to do.
- What?

323
00:29:26.752 --> 00:29:28.686
For Emily.

324
00:29:34.960 --> 00:29:36.894
And now for me.

325
00:29:40.599 --> 00:29:42.533
- And Gus.
- [ Laughs ]

326
00:29:47.740 --> 00:29:49.674
How about that?

327
00:29:53.245 --> 00:29:55.236
[ Owl Hooting ]

328
00:30:04.356 --> 00:30:07.018
[ Sighs ]

329
00:30:07.092 --> 00:30:09.083
[ Beeps ]

330
00:30:09.161 --> 00:30:11.959
When I achieved my dreams.
it was like going home...

331
00:30:12.031 --> 00:30:14.363
to a place
I'd never been before.

332
00:30:14.433 --> 00:30:16.367
You don't know that feeling.
do you?

333
00:30:17.736 --> 00:30:20.102
The first few gifts
I've given you have been practical.

334
00:30:20.172 --> 00:30:24.165
Show up. do this. do that.

335
00:30:24.243 --> 00:30:28.236
And then the gifts started
needing you to provide input.

336
00:30:28.314 --> 00:30:30.441
They needed intuition.

337
00:30:30.516 --> 00:30:33.713
Still. your average person
is too weighted down.

338
00:30:33.786 --> 00:30:37.916
 Jason. you need to be free.
free to dream.

339
00:30:37.990 --> 00:30:41.858
You need to come up
with a dream. then act on it.

340
00:30:41.927 --> 00:30:46.227
 Jason. this is the time
for you to dream.

341
00:30:49.768 --> 00:30:52.430
[ Owl Hooting ]

342
00:30:53.939 --> 00:30:56.737
[ Jason ]
You thinkin'about butterflies?

343
00:30:56.809 --> 00:30:59.903
[ Emily ]
No. Jason. I'm looking at the stars.

344
00:30:59.978 --> 00:31:04.074
You know.
I set this whole thing up...

345
00:31:04.149 --> 00:31:06.845
because I thought you wanted
to go horseback riding...

346
00:31:06.919 --> 00:31:08.910
not your mom.

347
00:31:08.987 --> 00:31:12.479
Get real. Horses are
smelly and sweaty.

348
00:31:16.362 --> 00:31:19.354
So. sweetie.
what's your dream?

349
00:31:19.431 --> 00:31:22.423
If you could dream
of anything- anything-

350
00:31:23.435 --> 00:31:25.460
what would your dream be?

351
00:31:26.672 --> 00:31:29.505
My dream?

352
00:31:29.575 --> 00:31:31.941
My dream was
a perfect day.

353
00:31:33.779 --> 00:31:36.805
And I'm just
finishing it.

354
00:31:36.882 --> 00:31:41.319
My dream was to be
with people I love...

355
00:31:41.387 --> 00:31:44.584
who love each other.
that love me.

356
00:32:00.372 --> 00:32:02.840
What about you. Jason?

357
00:32:03.842 --> 00:32:05.833
What's your dream?

358
00:32:08.380 --> 00:32:11.679
[ Sighs ]
I don't know.

359
00:32:13.352 --> 00:32:17.083
For as long as I can remember.
all I wanted to do was have fun.

360
00:32:19.391 --> 00:32:21.382
Now I don't have a clue.

361
00:32:22.828 --> 00:32:25.854
It's okay.
Guys are clueless.

362
00:32:25.931 --> 00:32:27.865
[ Laughs ]

363
00:32:27.933 --> 00:32:30.595
Hey. you have to know this.

364
00:32:31.904 --> 00:32:34.065
Even if you don't
have a dream of your own...

365
00:32:34.139 --> 00:32:36.073
you gave me mine.

366
00:32:36.141 --> 00:32:38.405
- That counts for something.
- Mmm.

367
00:32:40.078 --> 00:32:42.069
Of course.

368
00:32:47.920 --> 00:32:51.219
Look at her.
Isn't she beautiful?

369
00:32:51.290 --> 00:32:53.224
[ Chattering ]

370
00:32:53.292 --> 00:32:56.056
I mean. except for
her choice in lipstick.

371
00:32:56.128 --> 00:32:58.062
[ Laughs ]

372
00:32:58.130 --> 00:33:02.032
But you have to admit...

373
00:33:02.100 --> 00:33:05.729
even if you got nothing
else out of the deal but her...

374
00:33:05.804 --> 00:33:08.204
you'd still be a huge winner.

375
00:33:08.273 --> 00:33:10.264
[ Laughing ]

376
00:33:13.479 --> 00:33:17.973
Don't blow it. Knowing you.
you're likely to do it.

377
00:33:22.154 --> 00:33:24.088
[ Sighs ]

378
00:33:24.156 --> 00:33:26.420
Merry Christmas. Jason.

379
00:33:33.098 --> 00:33:35.089
Merry Christmas.

380
00:33:40.839 --> 00:33:43.273
Up until now.
I have only existed.

381
00:33:44.276 --> 00:33:46.210
I've. um-

382
00:33:47.579 --> 00:33:49.570
I've drifted through life
day to day...

383
00:33:49.648 --> 00:33:52.617
thinking that
that was enough.

384
00:33:52.684 --> 00:33:55.744
And honestly. I don't know
if I have my own dream.

385
00:33:57.823 --> 00:34:01.452
But I do know I can help
others fulfill theirs. I know it.

386
00:34:07.199 --> 00:34:09.497
 Jason. will you excuse us
for a few minutes?

387
00:34:11.403 --> 00:34:13.394
Hamilton & Partners.

388
00:34:14.840 --> 00:34:17.104
[ Elevator Bell Dings ]

389
00:34:22.814 --> 00:34:28.775
We've deliberated and evaluated
whether or not your answer...

390
00:34:28.854 --> 00:34:33.257
conforms with the expressed
desires of Red Stevens...

391
00:34:33.325 --> 00:34:37.284
and we find
that your answer does.

392
00:34:37.362 --> 00:34:42.766
Therefore. we are releasing
an amount allocated for you at this time.

393
00:34:43.969 --> 00:34:46.938
That is. uh...

394
00:34:47.005 --> 00:34:52.170
$100 million to do with
whatever you please.

395
00:34:54.680 --> 00:34:58.776
All of us here at the firm
want to congratulate you. Jason...

396
00:34:58.850 --> 00:35:00.784
for sticking it out...

397
00:35:00.852 --> 00:35:03.946
putting up with some
very harsh conditions...

398
00:35:04.022 --> 00:35:06.456
and prevailing.

399
00:35:06.525 --> 00:35:08.516
Congratulations. Jason.

400
00:35:15.200 --> 00:35:17.134
So that's it?

401
00:35:17.202 --> 00:35:20.569
[ Chuckles ]
Yes. I- I think so.

402
00:35:20.639 --> 00:35:23.802
No. don't get me wrong.
It's not the amount.

403
00:35:23.875 --> 00:35:25.866
It's. uh-

404
00:35:27.946 --> 00:35:29.937
It's just-

405
00:35:30.015 --> 00:35:32.040
I don't know.
I was...

406
00:35:32.117 --> 00:35:34.085
expecting a different
feeling or...

407
00:35:36.321 --> 00:35:38.312
something.

408
00:35:40.092 --> 00:35:44.392
I think that's
because now you...

409
00:35:44.463 --> 00:35:46.397
are a different person.

410
00:35:48.200 --> 00:35:50.862
And. uh-
And. no...

411
00:35:50.936 --> 00:35:52.927
we won't cash
that check for you.

412
00:35:53.005 --> 00:35:56.497
[ All Laughing ]

413
00:35:56.575 --> 00:35:59.669
Okay. so he is the best
architect in town. That's great.

414
00:35:59.745 --> 00:36:02.270
Tell him I want a meeting with him
first thing Monday morning.

415
00:36:05.384 --> 00:36:07.614
I want to tour that property
as soon as possible.

416
00:36:07.686 --> 00:36:11.918
Oh. that's amazing. We'll have a meeting
at the bank in. let's say. what. a month?

417
00:36:11.990 --> 00:36:14.424
- [ Man ] That would depend on how
many vehicles you were talking.
- [ Beeps ]

418
00:36:14.493 --> 00:36:16.927
- I'm sorry. Can you hold on?
- Certainly.

419
00:36:16.995 --> 00:36:20.260
- Yeah?
- [ Man #2 ]
Mr. Stevens. a-a young lady to see you.

420
00:36:20.332 --> 00:36:22.266
- Great. Send her up.
- Okay.

421
00:36:22.334 --> 00:36:24.529
- I'm sorry.
- [ Man #1] Will it be a large number of-

422
00:36:24.603 --> 00:36:26.537
Yeah. there are gonna be
plenty of cars.

423
00:36:26.605 --> 00:36:29.733
- Okay. we'll have to look into it and let you know.
- Okay. thank you.

424
00:36:29.808 --> 00:36:31.799
You're welcome.

425
00:36:43.755 --> 00:36:47.384
Oh. I like the remodel.

426
00:36:49.428 --> 00:36:51.919
Where have you been?

427
00:36:51.997 --> 00:36:53.988
In and out of prison.

428
00:36:54.066 --> 00:36:56.899
Mmm.
Good to hear.

429
00:36:57.969 --> 00:37:00.563
No visible tattoos.

430
00:37:00.639 --> 00:37:02.732
- I missed you.
- Hmm.

431
00:37:04.676 --> 00:37:06.769
- What's this?
- Oh. it's nothing.

432
00:37:07.846 --> 00:37:09.780
That's a nice round number.

433
00:37:09.848 --> 00:37:13.375
Somehow I don't think you'll be having
any more credit card problems. will you?

434
00:37:13.452 --> 00:37:16.512
You know. um.
you still owe me a dinner.

435
00:37:16.588 --> 00:37:18.522
How could I ever forget?

436
00:37:19.591 --> 00:37:21.582
I missed you.

437
00:37:25.664 --> 00:37:27.655
I think I still
remember my way around.

438
00:37:27.733 --> 00:37:29.758
Why don't you meet me
in a few minutes?

439
00:37:38.577 --> 00:37:40.511
How quaint.

440
00:37:40.579 --> 00:37:42.570
Hmm.

441
00:37:46.752 --> 00:37:48.913
 Jason?
Where'd you go?

442
00:38:06.705 --> 00:38:08.639
[ Exhales ]

443
00:38:10.275 --> 00:38:13.676
Shall I keep the limo running.
Mr. Stevens?

444
00:38:13.745 --> 00:38:15.337
Maybe not.

445
00:38:18.717 --> 00:38:22.016
Ah. Mr. Hamilton. Miss Hastings.
I'm so happy you came.

446
00:38:22.087 --> 00:38:25.614
 Jason. what's going on?

447
00:38:25.690 --> 00:38:27.681
Have a seat.
Please. I insist.

448
00:38:33.231 --> 00:38:37.224
Thank you all for joining me today.
May I direct your attention to-

449
00:38:38.303 --> 00:38:40.601
[ All Murmuring ]

450
00:38:40.672 --> 00:38:42.606
It's called Emily's Home.

451
00:38:42.674 --> 00:38:46.405
It's for a dozen or more families
experiencing extraordinary health challenges.

452
00:38:46.478 --> 00:38:51.108
Now. over here
will be the homes.

453
00:38:51.183 --> 00:38:53.583
They're part of the same complex.
yet individual dwellings.

454
00:38:53.652 --> 00:38:57.520
Families are gonna be able to live together
while they face their problems.

455
00:38:57.589 --> 00:38:59.887
Now. obviously. there's
gonna be plenty of parking.

456
00:38:59.958 --> 00:39:03.450
Over here is gonna be a state-of-the-art
employment center...

457
00:39:03.528 --> 00:39:06.429
catering to parents. single or married.
who need to earn some sort of income...

458
00:39:06.498 --> 00:39:08.557
while their child
undergoes treatment.

459
00:39:08.633 --> 00:39:12.535
Now. at this
state-of-the-art hospital-

460
00:39:12.604 --> 00:39:16.233
Excuse me.
What's missing?

461
00:39:16.308 --> 00:39:18.401
Oh. yeah.
A church...

462
00:39:18.476 --> 00:39:21.206
a worship center.

463
00:39:21.279 --> 00:39:23.213
How much is this
gonna cost?

464
00:39:23.281 --> 00:39:26.216
If you look at the prospectus
in front of you. page 5.

465
00:39:26.284 --> 00:39:29.447
The total initial outlay
will be $350 million.

466
00:39:29.521 --> 00:39:34.390
Your part will be to underwrite the financing
and a loan guarantee of 250 million.

467
00:39:34.459 --> 00:39:37.087
I'm gonna be putting up the first
100 million of my own money.

468
00:39:37.162 --> 00:39:41.963
Mr. Stevens. this is all well and fine. We did
business with your grandfather for many years.

469
00:39:42.033 --> 00:39:46.436
Excuse me. I'm sorry for interrupting.
but I didn't phrase this as a question.

470
00:39:46.504 --> 00:39:50.804
You are gonna do this. You made this much
off my grandfather in a typical year.

471
00:39:50.876 --> 00:39:55.336
- [ Cell Phone Rings ]
- And. gentlemen. this project has...

472
00:39:55.413 --> 00:39:58.780
- the full resources of the
Hamilton law firm backing it.
- Yes? Oh. I-

473
00:39:58.850 --> 00:40:03.287
Pro bono. as I'm sure
you will be too.

474
00:40:04.556 --> 00:40:07.354
Wrap up the details for me.
will you. Hamilton?

475
00:40:07.425 --> 00:40:09.825
- My pleasure.
- Thank you all. I appreciate it.

476
00:40:09.895 --> 00:40:11.795
[ All Murmuring ]

477
00:40:13.865 --> 00:40:16.197
Hey. Whoa.

478
00:40:16.268 --> 00:40:18.293
Come on. come on.
come on. come on!

479
00:40:21.673 --> 00:40:24.665
[ Alexia Crying ]

480
00:40:46.831 --> 00:40:48.822
[ Crying Continues ]

481
00:40:51.803 --> 00:40:53.794
[ Sniffles ]

482
00:41:07.652 --> 00:41:09.643
She wanted me to be there.

483
00:41:11.790 --> 00:41:13.883
It was so important to her.

484
00:41:16.795 --> 00:41:19.127
She wanted me to be there.

485
00:42:26.264 --> 00:42:30.598
 Jason. Alexia.
as mayor of Charlotte...

486
00:42:30.668 --> 00:42:34.160
it is my extreme honor
and privilege to preside over...

487
00:42:34.239 --> 00:42:37.766
the ground breaking
for Emily's Home.

488
00:42:37.842 --> 00:42:41.573
But it is also a sad day...

489
00:42:41.646 --> 00:42:47.141
in that the namesake and the inspiration
for this incredible project...

490
00:42:47.218 --> 00:42:49.743
is not here with us today.

491
00:42:50.822 --> 00:42:54.189
But her spirit
will always be with us all.

492
00:42:58.997 --> 00:43:00.988
 Jason. Alexia.

493
00:43:07.972 --> 00:43:09.963
[ Indistinct ]

494
00:43:11.543 --> 00:43:13.477
[ Mayor]
Thank you very much.

495
00:43:13.545 --> 00:43:17.140
- [ Chattering ]
- Thanks.

496
00:43:24.456 --> 00:43:28.119
I am so proud of the man
you've become.

497
00:43:28.193 --> 00:43:30.889
Thanks in great part to you.

498
00:43:30.962 --> 00:43:33.931
Meet me at my office as soon
as possible. will you?

499
00:43:33.998 --> 00:43:37.297
- I have one more matter I need to discuss.
- Of course.

500
00:43:40.438 --> 00:43:43.930
We understand you went
outside the boundaries of our instructions...

501
00:43:44.008 --> 00:43:46.738
with one of those gifts.

502
00:43:46.811 --> 00:43:48.745
What?

503
00:43:48.813 --> 00:43:51.373
Don't ''what'' me.
You know what I'm talking about.

504
00:44:02.260 --> 00:44:06.697
- Miss Hastings. will you. uh.
dismiss everyone. please?
- Oh. Yes. sir.

505
00:44:11.769 --> 00:44:13.760
[ Door Closes ]

506
00:44:25.250 --> 00:44:27.616
[ Man ]
Over the course of several days...

507
00:44:27.685 --> 00:44:30.085
this investigator personally witnessed
and recorded the subject...

508
00:44:30.155 --> 00:44:35.024
as he committed various misdemeanor
infractions for which he was never cited.

509
00:44:37.862 --> 00:44:41.423
Nevertheless. illegal
activities did occur.

510
00:44:42.500 --> 00:44:45.765
Panhandling.
bordering on assault...

511
00:44:48.873 --> 00:44:53.207
stealing private property.
resale of stolen items...

512
00:44:57.215 --> 00:45:00.946
street vending
without a permit...

513
00:45:01.019 --> 00:45:02.953
jaywalking.

514
00:45:03.021 --> 00:45:07.549
It is the opinion of this investigator
that the subject is a reprobate...

515
00:45:07.625 --> 00:45:11.425
and not capable of completing
the 12 gifts laid out in Red Stevens's will.

516
00:45:11.496 --> 00:45:13.259
[ Hamilton ]
That's enough. Miss Hastings.

517
00:45:13.331 --> 00:45:15.526
[ Hastings ]
My pleasure. Mr. Hamilton.

518
00:45:16.534 --> 00:45:21.437
 Jason. if you made it this far.
he had one final message.

519
00:45:39.190 --> 00:45:41.522
- [ Red ] Jason.
- Yeah?

520
00:45:43.328 --> 00:45:45.990
You gave away the $100 million?
All of it?

521
00:45:48.066 --> 00:45:51.092
- Yeah. so what?
- Well. if you're standing here now...

522
00:45:51.169 --> 00:45:56.300
it means that not only have you succeeded
in receiving all of my gifts...

523
00:45:56.374 --> 00:45:59.832
but have done so beyond
the boundaries that I have set.

524
00:46:01.646 --> 00:46:05.173
I guess that means
that I have succeeded as well.

525
00:46:07.385 --> 00:46:10.013
What I could not
accomplish in life...

526
00:46:10.088 --> 00:46:12.352
I have done in death.

527
00:46:13.791 --> 00:46:18.558
As long as you are
still alive. I will be too.

528
00:46:21.833 --> 00:46:23.824
I love you. Son.

529
00:46:23.901 --> 00:46:25.732
I love you too.

530
00:46:29.107 --> 00:46:31.166
Good-bye. Jason.

531
00:47:20.425 --> 00:47:23.553
''As executor of the estate
of Red Stevens...

532
00:47:23.628 --> 00:47:26.188
''I hereby execute
and otherwise assign...

533
00:47:26.264 --> 00:47:30.928
''complete and controlling
interest to Jason Stevens...

534
00:47:31.002 --> 00:47:33.300
''the balance of Red's estate...

535
00:47:34.639 --> 00:47:37.870
''including all holdings.
investment portfolio...

536
00:47:37.942 --> 00:47:41.503
''and offshore interests...

537
00:47:41.579 --> 00:47:46.710
totaling in excess
of two billion dollars. ''

538
00:47:48.553 --> 00:47:53.252
Depending on OPEC prices
and foreign currency fluctuations. of course.

539
00:48:06.738 --> 00:48:09.332
[ Red's Voice ]
I need a lawyer for a few business ideas I have...

540
00:48:09.407 --> 00:48:11.341
a few still
in the dream stage.

541
00:48:11.409 --> 00:48:13.343
[ Hamilton's Voice ]
When would you like to meet?

542
00:48:13.411 --> 00:48:15.641
[ Red's Voice ]
Meet? Hell.you're hired.

543
00:48:15.713 --> 00:48:18.648
[ Hamilton's Voice ]
Sir. are you sure you wouldn't like to meet first?

544
00:48:18.716 --> 00:48:22.208
[ Red's Voice ] You were at the top
of your law class. were you not?

545
00:48:22.286 --> 00:48:24.550
- [ Hamilton's Voice ] Yes. sir.
- [ Red's Voice ] Then you're my lawyer.

546
00:48:24.622 --> 00:48:27.989
Now let's get on with it.
We got a world to conquer.

547
00:48:39.404 --> 00:48:42.862
Do you think I'm old.
Miss Hastings?

548
00:48:42.940 --> 00:48:44.999
Mm-mmm.

549
00:48:45.076 --> 00:48:50.207
Well. I think it's about time I retire
from this law firm.

550
00:48:53.050 --> 00:48:56.349
Whatever will you do.
Mr. Hamilton?

551
00:48:58.589 --> 00:49:00.750
Go to work
with  Jason Stevens.

552
00:49:00.825 --> 00:49:03.293
[ Chuckles ]

553
00:49:03.361 --> 00:49:05.386
- Change the world.
- Mmm.

554
00:49:07.532 --> 00:49:09.523
[ Footsteps Approaching ]

555
00:49:10.535 --> 00:49:12.526
Hi.

556
00:49:12.603 --> 00:49:14.537
Hi.

557
00:49:31.022 --> 00:49:33.013
Thank you.

558
00:50:07.692 --> 00:50:10.490
So I want
to give you a gift-

559
00:50:10.561 --> 00:50:15.589
a series of gifts
leading up to. well...

560
00:50:15.666 --> 00:50:18.464
I wanna call it
''the ultimate gift.''

561
00:50:18.536 --> 00:50:21.528
Now. you fail in any way.
it's over. You get nothing.

562
00:50:28.079 --> 00:50:31.310
You know. you do any work
like you just did...

563
00:50:31.382 --> 00:50:33.316
you can do anything.

564
00:50:45.363 --> 00:50:48.127
Now. aren't you
forgettin' something?

565
00:50:48.199 --> 00:50:51.464
- I don't think so. Shoot.
- The gift.

566
00:50:51.536 --> 00:50:53.333
The gift of work.

567
00:50:53.404 --> 00:50:55.964
- Wow.
- Congratulations.

568
00:51:01.979 --> 00:51:05.312
The charge card company
declined the charge.

569
00:51:05.383 --> 00:51:08.477
That's impossible. I don't have a credit limit.
Just run it through again.

570
00:51:08.553 --> 00:51:13.957
It's always our practice to run it through again.
but they declined.

571
00:51:20.998 --> 00:51:22.693
I need a friend.

572
00:51:22.767 --> 00:51:26.168
You expect this friendship
to continue?

573
00:51:26.237 --> 00:51:29.673
I plan on knowing  Jason
for the rest of my life.

574
00:51:36.514 --> 00:51:39.972
Do- Do you truly
know how to learn?

575
00:51:41.052 --> 00:51:44.180
Villagers wait for books.

576
00:51:44.255 --> 00:51:46.189
You bring them new books.

577
00:51:46.257 --> 00:51:50.819
They are waiting for you
to pick up old books.

578
00:51:50.895 --> 00:51:54.296
Exchange. Library.
¿S¡?

579
00:51:57.168 --> 00:51:59.159
[ Exhales ]

580
00:52:06.644 --> 00:52:09.977
Well. you don't begin to live
until you've lost everything.

581
00:52:10.047 --> 00:52:13.505
Wait. Wait.

582
00:52:13.584 --> 00:52:17.213
That's an $8.000 paint job!
[ Groans ]

583
00:52:17.288 --> 00:52:19.483
Heck. I've lost everything
three or four times.

584
00:52:19.557 --> 00:52:21.821
It's the perfect
place to start.

585
00:52:29.634 --> 00:52:34.003
And Emily- she's-

586
00:52:40.344 --> 00:52:43.404
What's gonna
happen to my mom?

587
00:52:43.481 --> 00:52:45.574
I really don't hate her.
you know.

588
00:52:45.650 --> 00:52:47.584
[ Crying ]

589
00:52:47.652 --> 00:52:50.348
[ Sniffles ]

590
00:52:55.760 --> 00:52:57.853
[ All Laughing ]

591
00:52:57.928 --> 00:53:00.419
- Salud.
- Salud.

592
00:53:02.433 --> 00:53:04.867
Salud.

593
00:53:05.870 --> 00:53:09.169
[ Laughing ]

594
00:53:14.745 --> 00:53:19.705
 Jason. you need to be free.
free to dream.

595
00:53:19.784 --> 00:53:22.776
You need to come up
with a dream. then act on it.

596
00:53:22.853 --> 00:53:26.050
And honestly. I don't know
if I have my own dream.

597
00:53:28.059 --> 00:53:30.823
But I do know I can help others
fulfill theirs.

598
00:53:36.500 --> 00:53:39.230
Uh. I do have to
give away some money.

599
00:53:39.303 --> 00:53:41.794
You're getting
less mysterious by the minute.

600
00:53:43.974 --> 00:53:46.135
She owes $1.600
in back rent.

601
00:53:46.210 --> 00:53:48.303
Pay it.

602
00:53:48.379 --> 00:53:50.506
You're a hundred
dollars short.

603
00:53:50.581 --> 00:53:53.880
Tell Hamilton I'm good for it.
Just pay that bill.

604
00:54:00.257 --> 00:54:02.817
So. apparently...

605
00:54:03.894 --> 00:54:06.829
someone came by
and covered my back rent.

606
00:54:07.832 --> 00:54:09.823
Was it you?

607
00:54:11.836 --> 00:54:13.633
Thank you.

608
00:54:21.779 --> 00:54:23.770
What would
your dream be?

609
00:54:25.182 --> 00:54:27.980
My dream?

610
00:54:28.052 --> 00:54:30.020
My dream was
a perfect day.

611
00:54:36.827 --> 00:54:39.193
And I'm just
finishing it.

612
00:54:47.972 --> 00:54:51.135
- I love you. Son.
- I love you too.

613
00:54:54.278 --> 00:54:56.542
Good-bye. Jason.
